title: Chinese defense contractor to begin launching VLEO satellites
summary: A major Chinese state-owned defense contractor is preparing to launch the first satellite for a very low Earth orbit constellation.

title: SpaceX to launch initial satellites for Space Development Agency
summary: SpaceX is scheduled to launch a batch of 10 communications and missile tracking satellites on the Tranche 0 Flight 1 mission for the Space Development Agency (SDA) on Thursday, March 30, 2023, at approximately 7:29 AM PDT (14:29 UTC). The flight will take off from launch site SLC-4E at Vandenberg Space Force Base in California.

title: NASA releases draft strategy for long-term robotic Mars exploration
summary: NASA has unveiled a draft strategy for long-term robotic exploration of Mars that emphasizes low-cost missions and potential commercial partnerships.

title: Vulcan Experiences Anomaly During Test, Maiden Flight Delayed
summary: ULA has experienced an anomaly during testing of a Vulcan Centaur 2nd stage, and an investigation is underway.

title: Isar Aerospace Raises $165 Million Ahead Of First Launch
summary: Isar Aerospace has raised $165 million in a Series C funding round to scale up production of its Spectrum rocket

title: Starliner crewed test flight delayed to July
summary: NASA and Boeing have pushed back the first crewed launch of the company’s CST-100 Starliner spacecraft with astronauts on board until at least late July because of certification paperwork that has taken longer than expected to complete.

title: Rosotics unveils 3D printer for rocket tanks and fairings
summary: Rosotics developed a new type of 3D printer to reduce the cost and power required to manufacture rocket tanks, fairings and other large aerospace structures.

title: US Space Development Agency Ready To Launch First Satellites
summary: The Space Development Agency (SDA), a Pentagon initiative created in 2019 to accelerate the use of commercial space technology, is set to launch its first fleet of 10 satellites on March 30th.

title: Military space agency created to go fast is about to launch its first satellites
summary: The Space Development Agency, formed inside the Pentagon in 2019 to help accelerate the use of commercial space technology, is preparing to launch on March 30 its inaugural fleet of 10 satellites.
